						               													<description>This house-building game is slightly more complex than the average roll-and-move. Each player starts with a House Plan that shows eight rooms: Living Room, Dining Room, Family Room, Kitchen, Bath, Master Bedroom, Child's Bedroom and Garage.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to purchase Construction cards for each room to complete the house. Each player starts with $18,000, but this amount is a &amp;quot;mortgage&amp;quot; that must also be paid back in order to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In order to build a room, a player's token must move to the Home space and draw a Construction card. This may offer a chance to build a specific room at a certain price; if the player cannot afford, does not want to pay the price, or already has built that room, his turn ends. Construction cards may also direct a player to draw and act on a card from the Risk/Option deck. Players may stay at the Home space as long as they wish and continue drawing a Construction card each turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Since the initial mortgage is not enough to build the entire home, players must also spend time &amp;quot;working&amp;quot;. This involves starting from the Work space and rolling 2D6 around the board. Players earn $200 per space moved, and continue to work until they are able to reach the Home space. Board spaces have various events with bonuses and penalties dealing with home-building issues like strikes and permits. Players may also choose to play the stock market instead of moving, drawing a card from the Stock Market deck that either wins or loses money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
